#!/usr/bin/env python3

"""Two-stage calibration + inference pipeline for galaxy isophotal radii,
producing the "best" estimate of R_r(26) (and hence D26) from
multi-band, multi-threshold isophotal radius measurements. This is the
procedure that produced the SGA-2025 D26 diameters (via
``SGA.SGA.SGA_diameter`` -> ``SGA.calibrate.infer_best_r26`` in
production).

Data model (astropy Table expected, read from the ``ELLIPSE`` extension):
  Columns: R{TH}_{X}, R{TH}_ERR_{X}  for TH in {23,24,25,26}, X in {G,R,I,Z}
  Plus:    SMA_MOMENT  (no per-object error available)
  Units:   plain floats (no astropy.units). Missing values are encoded as 0.0.

Stage 1 (calibrate -> SGA.calibrate.calibrate_from_table): for each
channel, fits a robust least-squares bisector regression (Isobe et al.
1990 -- the average of the y-on-x and x-on-y ordinary least-squares
slopes, in log-space) mapping that channel's isophotal radius onto the
R26_R anchor, log(R26) = a + b*log(R_channel), with iterative
sigma-clipping on the orthogonal residuals to reject outliers. Learns
each channel's intrinsic scatter (tau) and, for channels without
per-object errors (e.g. SMA_MOMENT), a default log-uncertainty. Writes
coefficients to an ASCII TSV file (SGA.calibrate.save_calibration).

Stage 2 (infer -> SGA.calibrate.infer_best_r26): for any table, applies
the calibration and combines all available channels at the deepest
available isophotal threshold via inverse-variance weighting in
log-space to return R_r(26), then converts to D26 (diameter, arcmin).
Not run standalone via this script in production -- SGA_diameter calls
infer_best_r26 directly in-process.

Covariates: both calibrate_from_table and infer_best_r26 accept
covariates/covariate_names parameters, scaffolding a possible future
extension of the model to log(R26) = a + b*log(R_channel) + c.covariates
(e.g. an inclination- or surface-brightness-dependent correction term).
This extension is not yet implemented in calibrate_from_table (see its
docstring). No covariates have been used in any SGA-2025 production
calibration to date -- neither production call site (this script, nor
SGA_diameter) passes them, and every channel in the shipped
py/SGA/data/SGA2025/r26-calibration-coeff.tsv has empty
covar_names/c_json.

Public API (import these):
  - calibrate_from_table(table, calib_path, *, covariates=None, covariate_names=None)
  - infer_best_r26(table, calib_path, *, covariates=None, add_columns=True, include_direct_r26=True)
  - load_calibration(calib_path), save_calibration(cal, path)

CLI (optional):
  python SGA2025-calibrate-r26 calibrate  input.fits  r26_calibration.tsv
  python SGA2025-calibrate-r26 infer      input.fits  r26_calibration.tsv  output.fits

Production provenance: the coefficients shipped at
py/SGA/data/SGA2025/r26-calibration-coeff.tsv were produced by running
the ``calibrate`` command below against two successive parent-sample
versions, both writing to the same output filename (save_calibration
overwrites on each write, so the v0.22 run's coefficients are the ones
actually shipped):

  SGA2025-calibrate-r26 calibrate /global/homes/i/ioannis/SGA2025/sample/SGA2025-v0.10-dr11-south.fits r26-calibration-coeff.tsv
  SGA2025-calibrate-r26 calibrate /global/homes/i/ioannis/SGA2025/sample/SGA2025-v0.22-dr11-south.fits r26-calibration-coeff.tsv

Originally scaffolded with ChatGPT assistance; the description above
reflects the pipeline as actually implemented and verified for
SGA-2025.

"""
import sys
from astropy.table import Table, vstack
from SGA.calibrate import calibrate_from_table, infer_best_r26

from SGA.logger import log


def _read_table(path: str) -> Table:
    return Table.read(path, 'ELLIPSE', format="fits")


def main(argv=None) -> None:
    argv = list(sys.argv[1:] if argv is None else argv)
    if len(argv) < 1 or argv[0] in {"-h", "--help"}:
        print("Usage:\n"
              "  calibrate  INPUT.fits CALIB.tsv\n"
              "  infer      INPUT.fits CALIB.tsv  OUTPUT.(fits|ecsv)\n", file=sys.stderr)
        sys.exit(2)

    cmd = argv[0].lower()
    if cmd == "calibrate":
        if len(argv) < 3:
            sys.exit("calibrate requires INPUT and CALIB.tsv")
        in_path, calib_path = argv[1], argv[2]
        tbl = _read_table(in_path)
        ## temporary hack
        #in_path1, in_path2, calib_path = argv[1], argv[2], argv[3]
        #tbl1 = _read_table(in_path1)
        #tbl2 = _read_table(in_path2)
        #tbl = vstack((tbl1, tbl2))
        calibrate_from_table(tbl, calib_path)
    elif cmd == "infer":
        if len(argv) < 4:
            sys.exit("infer requires INPUT, CALIB.tsv, and OUTPUT path")
        in_path, calib_path, out_path = argv[1], argv[2], argv[3]
        tbl = _read_table(in_path)
        infer_best_r26(tbl, calib_path, add_columns=True, include_direct_r26=True)
        tbl.write(out_path, overwrite=True)
        log.info(f"Wrote {out_path}")
    else:
        sys.exit(f"Unknown command: {cmd}")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
